│ there might be multiple calls to `set` for the same VPValue with different lanes, creating multiple scalar values. When `onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)` is true, we expect to have only one      │
│ scalar value (in lane 0), but the assertion is failing because `Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size() != 1`.                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The issue is in the assertion logic. When `onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)` is true, we should allow the case where we have scalar values but more than one, as long as we're accessing lane 0.    │
│ Actually, looking at the assertion again:                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ assert((VF.isScalar() || Def->isLiveIn() || hasVectorValue(Def) ||                                                                                                                        │
│         !vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) ||                                                                                                                                               │
│         (hasScalarValue(Def, VPLane(0)) &&                                                                                                                                                │
│          Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size() == 1)) &&                                                                                                                                           │
│        "Trying to access a single scalar per part but has multiple scalars "                                                                                                              │
│        "per part.");                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The assertion says: if we need a scalar value (NeedsScalar=true), then one of these must be true:                                                                                         │
│ 1. VF.isScalar() - we're not vectorizing                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 2. Def->isLiveIn() - it's a live-in value                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. hasVectorValue(Def) - we have a vector value for it                                                                                                                                    │
│ 4. !vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) - not only first lane is used                                                                                                                         │
│ 5. (hasScalarValue(Def, VPLane(0)) && Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size() == 1) - we have a scalar value in lane 0 and exactly one scalar value total                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The problem is condition 5. When `onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)` is true, we expect to have only one scalar value. But what if we have scalar values in multiple lanes even though only the      │
│ first lane is used? This could happen if the value was set for multiple lanes but only lane 0 is actually used.                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Actually, looking more carefully at the error message: "Trying to access a single scalar per part but has multiple scalars per part." This suggests that when we call `get(Def, true)`    │
